#matrix 
Matrix Operations in C
Project Overview

Matrix Operations is a simple C project developed to perform basic mathematical operations on matrices using functions and 2D arrays.
The project is menu-driven and demonstrates modular programming by separating each operation into different functions.

->Features
1.Matrix Addition
2.Matrix Multiplication
3.Matrix Transpose

->Menu Driven Program
.Uses Functions for Better Modularity
.Uses 2D Arrays for Matrix Storage

->Concepts Used
1.C Programming
2.Functions
3.2D Arrays
4.Nested Loops
5.Switch Case
6.Matrix Calculations

Menu Driven Programming
Project Structure
matrix_operations/
│
├── main.c
└── README.md

->How It Works
.User enters matrix dimensions.
.User enters matrix values.
.Selects operation from the menu.
.Program performs the selected operation.
.Result is displayed on screen.

->Operations
Matrix Addition

Adds corresponding elements of two matrices.
Matrix Multiplication
Multiplies two matrices using row and column multiplication rules.
Matrix Transpose

Converts rows into columns.
